  <h1 align = "center">Tips for Packing</h1>
       <img src = "https://www.zola.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/packing-tips_1200x675.jpg" height = 400px>
       </div>
       
       <p margin=50px>
<h2>1. Make a list of what you need</h2>
<p><h3>You probably think it's not necessary, but it's very helpful to make sure you can tangibly have everything.</h3></p>
<h2>2. Roll clothes in your suitcase</h2>
<p><h3>Rolling your clothes not only saves space, but it's great to prevent wrinkles in your clothes.</h3></p>
<h2>3. Pack your clothes using the 2:1 rule</h2>
<p><h3>The rule says to pack two tops for every bottom (skirts, shorts, etc). This rule is helpful because, most likely, you are going to end up wearing bottom pieces more often than your tops. This rule also saves space.</h3></p>
<h2>4. Pack a laundry bag</h2>
<p><h3>This bag can help you seperate your dirty clothes, while not messing up the organization inside the suitcase.</h3></p>
<h2>5. Use any and every available space</h2>
<p><h3>Use every single nook and cranny, whether even in your shoes. Use those small spaces to put small bags or headphones.</h3></p>
<h2>6. Seal Liquid bottles with a plastic bag</h2>
<p><h3>Take a ziploc bag and put the bag over the opening of the bottle before twisting the cap (or pump) closed. This creates a seal prenting leakage.</h3></p>
<h2>7. Cover footwear with shower caps.</h2>
<p><h3>This keeps your clothes clean.</h3></p>
<h2>8. Pack heavier items toward the wheels</h2>
<p><h3>The weight will be distributed more evenly in the suitcase, so it will be easier moving around with it.</h3></p>
<h2>9. Research you airline's limit on carry-ons</h2>
<p><h3>Make sure you know the limit and the pricing to be prepared.</h3></p>
<h2>10. Tangle free jewlery</h2>
<p><h3>Thread necklaces/bracelets through a straw to keep them from tangling in your luggage. You can also fasten bearrings through a button to keep them together</h3></p>
