       <h1 align = "center">How To Budget During Your Trip</h1>
        <img class = pictures src="https://reflectandrefresh.files.wordpress.com/2015/10/bigstock-collecting-money-for-travel-g-91255895.jpg"/height = 400px>
        </div>
        <h2>
          Come up with a certain amount of money that you'll be willing to spend on your entire trip - seperate that amount into these 5 groups:
        </h2>
        <div>
        </div>
        <p><h2>
         1. Transportation</h2> <h3>-A taxi or plane are both good ways to travel for short amounts of time, but the cost for both of 
         these most likely will depend on the amount of miles that you are trying to go. Most people going on a trip would reccomend
         paying for a rental car, so that all you would have to pay for is the original cost of the car, and gas. If you are 
         looking for a rental car company, here is one that has international service! 
         <a href="https://www.budget.com/en/offers/international">Rental Car</a></h3>
        </p>
        <div>
        </div>
        <p><h2>
          2. Accomodation </h2><h3>-Hotels, Apartment Rentals, and Resorts are all good options for when you need a place to stay,
         although the restorts will probably cost more than the rest, some allow you to eat at a free buffet, which would help 
         lower the amount of money that you would spend on food, especially if you have a large family. If you're looking for a
         website to find a hotel in the area you are going to, here is one that locates hotels almost all throughout the world!
